	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Hi everyone!
<br />
<br />I'm new to this forum (altough a very frequent visitor), and hope to contribute in some manner to this awesome discussion.
<br />
<br />The NES is my all time favourite console, and I'd like to put some ROMS on homebrew carts, and I have all the information needed thanks to this forum. And I'm doing this the rough way: I don't want to mess original carts, so I'll make my own game boards. I have some pirate carts, and the design is really easy to follow.
<br />
<br />My only problem at this moment is the EPROM burnning, but I'm searching for some projects (I have cool ones, but the parts are a little difficult to find in my country  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_sad.gif" alt=":(" title="Sad" /> )
<br />
<br />Besides, I'm an electronics freak, and love to make some homebrew projects too. My last attemp was this NES arkanoid controller at:
<br />
<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://es.geocities.com/gamemasterquilpue/NES_ARKANOID_CONTROLLER.htm">http://es.geocities.com/gamemasterquilp ... ROLLER.htm</a><!-- m -->
<br />
<br />I think you should put this link at the 'hardware projects' section of NESDEV.  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=":wink:" title="Wink" /> 
<br />
<br />Cheers

		

		</td>
	</tr>
