		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Memblers wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Wow, that's excellent.  I want to make one too.  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /><br />I used to have that game (and controller) years ago.<br /><br />For EPROM burning, I bought this one here <a href="http://sivava.com/" class="postlink">http://sivava.com/</a>, they ship from Thailand.  Also the schematics for it are available at <a href="http://willem.org" class="postlink">http://willem.org</a>, you've probably seen it before.<br /><br />What are the pirate cart designs like, are there a lot of 72-pin ones?  Are the consoles cloned, or do the carts have clone lockout chips?</div>
<br />
<br />Hey, Memblers!
<br />
<br />Well, I made the controller (with a nice board design), but unfortunately it didn't work.  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_cry.gif" alt=":cry:" title="Crying or Very sad" />  However, my console is a dual system clone, that uses different COM ports. But I'm sure it will work on the original console (I was talking with the autor Eric Pena, and he said he used a crappy polystation for the tests)  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=":wink:" title="Wink" /> 
<br />
<br />I'm sure if you drop a line to Eric, he'll help you as much as he can. And if you want my 'board design', I'll be very happy in send to you.
<br />
<br />Importing an EPROM burner in Brazil will be cost prohibitive. So, I'm searching for a DIY project. I just found this now:
<br />
<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.linuxdocs.org/HOWTOs/Diskless-HOWTO-6.htmlM">http://www.linuxdocs.org/HOWTOs/Diskless-HOWTO-6.htmlM</a><!-- m -->
<br />
<br />Yes, I know the willem project already. Thanks!  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /> 
<br />
<br />My boards vary from an 8 game multicart, an UNROM, a CNROM and NROM (I think). They're 72-pin. Very simple design, and using common EPROMS. I was very envolved in this stuff a year ago, and now I need to read a lot, in order to familiarize again)
<br />
<br />There's any lockout chips in the cart boards. The dual console has no limitations, but it rejects only one type or 60 pin cart, just these polystations crappy 'black wax' yellow carts. Dunno why (I'm sure the carts are alright, though)
<br />
<br />Of course, I could put some scans, if you're interested. But I'm crappy at corel draw, and since I don't have webcan and scanner, it can delay some time.   <img src="./images/smilies/icon_cry.gif" alt=":cry:" title="Crying or Very sad" /> 
<br />
<br />But I'm here to contribute, as much as I can.

		

